      },
      "date": "2014-12-04 15:25:29.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nIt's not compiled with latest master.\n\nlustre/include/lprocfs_status.h:606: error: conflicting types for 'remove_proc_subtree'\ninclude/linux/proc_fs.h:120: note: previous declaration of 'remove_proc_subtree' was here",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "dcb99a0c98eec93628fa034974570764663abbf4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 301,
        "name": "Dmitry Eremin",
        "email": "dmitry.eremin@intel.com",
        "username": "dmiter",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-12-04 15:31:02.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThis is after recently landed:\nLU-5275 lprocfs: remove last of non seq data structs and functions.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "8d88adadb31cf2423800ed990cf107a1386f94af",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 251,
        "name": "Bob Glossman",
        "email": "bob.glossman@intel.com",
        "username": "bogl",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-12-04 16:05:20.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nthink this is a problem in more than just el6.6.  el7 has remove_proc_subtree() in linux too.  changes from LU-5275 hasn't broken that build only because we aren't building servers there yet.\n\nI think I need a separate patch to add autoconf support for building with & without remove_proc_subtree() in the kernel, then rebase this mod on that one.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
